  "status": "Draft",
  "summary": "This standard defines `IZRC20`, a minimal interface for privacy-preserving fungible tokens on Ethereum. It uses zero-knowledge proofs to enable confidential transfers where transaction amounts, sender, and recipient identities remain hidden. The core mechanism relies on cryptographic commitments stored in a Merkle tree, with nullifiers preventing double-spending. This interface serves as a foundational building block for both wrapper protocols (adding privacy to existing [ERC-20](./eip-20) tokens) and dual-mode tokens (single tokens supporting both transparent and private transfers).",
  "title": "Privacy Token"
